            . I am a <rs id="t18310407-224-viclabel1204" type="occupation">meat-salesman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-224-victim1599 t18310407-224-viclabel1204"></join> at Newgate-market. On the 7th of February the prisoner came to me, and said he wanted a leg of mutton, or pork, for Mr. Knock, of Well-street, who is a customer of mine; we let him have a leg of mutton, believing he came from Mr. Knock, whose apprentice I knew he had been.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-224-person1600">
                  JOHN 
                  KNOCK
               <interp inst="t18310407-224-person1600" type="surname" value="KNOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-224-person1600" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-224-person1600" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a bookbinder, and deal with Mr. Stokes. The prisoner was my apprentice for twelve months, and I used to send him for meat; he was not in my employ on the 7th of February - I did not send him for this meat; he never brought it to me - he had absconded from me a month.</p>
               <p>MARIA KNOCK. I am Mr. Knock's wife. I did not authorize the prisoner to go to Mr. Stokes' for meat - he never brought it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never went there after I left Mr. Knock.</p>
